args: What do you mean you wish to remain\nhere? Why would you not return to your\nown world?
This place is a paradise, free of worldly\nobligations like work.
I had the same thought—that it would be\nnice to carve out a placid existence in this\nempty world, eating and sleeping...
Right? We've got meat, fish, rice...\nThere's more food stocked in the shops\nhere than we can feasibly eat.
And when we eat it, it replenishes\nitself before we know it!\nIf that's not paradise, then what is?
Truly? I've never heard of such a thing.
We thought it was curious at first, too.\nBut when we considered that it could be\nyet another of Amaterasu's blessings...
What?! Hold a moment! Why would you\nthink it the doing of Amaterasu?!
Why, because it was she who brought us\nhere!
What is the meaning of this?\nAmaterasu is behind this predicament?!
Amaterasu, the culprit behind the\ndisappearances? Preposterous!
Disappearances? Ah, yes. I suppose to the\nworld at large, it would seem as though\nwe had disappeared, wouldn't it?
You mean to say that you really weren't\nbrought here against your will?

That's right. Several nights ago, as my
husband and I wandered the world of
dreams, we each heard a voice
proclaiming itself to be Amaterasu.
She asked us: ＂Do you wish\nto live in peace and happiness?＂
Naturally, we each said yes, and before\nwe knew it, we found ourselves here.
Hm, and yet we had no such dream before\nWE were transported here.
It's gotta have something to do with the\npillar that Daikokuten bit into. Seemed like\nit had something to do with Amaterasu.
Maybe when he messed with it, we were\nspirited away here in a fashion that even\nAmaterasu could not have expected.
Oh? Could it be that you do not possess\none of these stones, Lady Mitsuhide?
We received them from Amaterasu.\nShe bade us use them if we wished\nto return to our world.
Oho! Yes, yes! These gleamshards are\nindeed the genuine article! I can feel\nAmaterasu's power radiating forth!

Gleamshards are near-priceless. Even we
Wyrmclan leaders only get them when we
embark upon our fortune-spreading trips
to distant lands.
I see. I believe we can safely conclude,\nthen, that all of these events are of\nAmaterasu's design.
However, one mystery remains:\nWhat was her motive?

I'm sure she had her reasons—
unfathomable to the likes of us, no
doubt—but worrying about it won't
get us anywhere.
After all, Amaterasu is a great and\npowerful dragon who created a world\nof peace and harmony.
And with that, the problem's solved.\nHey, you two mind if we take that\ngleamshard off your hands?
Not at all, my lady. Here.
Thanks. Now, how's about we use this and\nhead home, you two?
Mitsuhide, are you saying you wish to\nleave these people behind here?!\nHow callous!
You wound me. Now, if I were to force\nthem to come back with us against their\nwill, THAT would be callous.
After all, they're the ones who decided to\ncome live in this world.
Surely you wouldn't shatter the happiness\nthey've attained by dragging them back\nkicking and screaming?
That is exactly what I plan to do!
What?! B-but—please, I beg you! No!
And I as well! Please, we wish to live\nhere, in paradise!
You keep saying the word, but I see no\nparadise here!

Here in this soulless husk of a world,
you can only pass your days in idle
solitude, never knowing the transformative
power of change!
And yet we crave nothing more!
We were so, so tired of living in a world\nof naught but worry, toiling our days away\njust to survive.
You grew tired of living?! Pathetic! What\nmerit is there in a stagnant existence,\ndevoid of progress?
That's enough, Nobunaga. You have your\nvalues, and they have theirs.
Pah. So you've been ensnared by this\nworld's vile temptations, too.
More or less. It suits my chilled-out\nlifestyle just fine, after all.
But you know what? Even if I did view the\nworld the way you do, I'd still leave these\nfolks here and go home.
Why? Please, Mitsuhide. I want to\nunderstand.
Everyone's got their own idea of what\nhappiness is. I just wanna do whatever it\nis that makes these people the happiest.
Thank you so much, Lady Mitsuhide!
You truly are a worthy leader! You honor\nus with your concern for our feelings!
A ＂worthy ruler＂? So to be worthy, one\nshould always grant the people their\ndesires?
But... No, if you only ever look at the world\nthrough the same eyes as the people,\nyou cannot lead them into the future!
If your goal's to have a strong, wealthy\nkingdom...then yeah, you're right.
But there's no one right answer.\nThe pursuit of happiness is different\nfor everyone.
Some people will seek the same kind of\nhappiness you do...and some of them\nwon't. That's all there is to it.
Hm. I see. I think I understand better,\nif only somewhat.
Yeah. Now, let's get ourselves home.

(Not everyone has the strength to walk this
path. Though I may find fault in the weak
for balking at hardship, they will balk
nonetheless.)
(If so, then it is the destiny of the\nstrong...)

(...to cut through the suffering running
rampant through this world of worry and
sorrow, and guide the people towards
happiness!)
